# Reference-Driven Development

**Trigger:** user asks to build/create a project **from a reference**, replicate a reference game, «по референсу», «возьми референс», reference-driven cycle, or CONTINUE/REWORK/ESCALATE in an orchestrator session.

**Skill:** `.agents/skills/reference-driven-cycle/SKILL.md` — **orchestrator** (parent chat, no production code)  
**Playbook:** `docs/reference-driven-cycle.md`  
**Subagents:** `.agents/skills/reference-driven-subagent/SKILL.md` via Task tool

## On trigger

1. Read `reference-driven-cycle` skill + `docs/reference-driven-cycle.md`
2. Act as **ORCHESTRATOR** — delegate to subagents, do not implement features yourself
3. Notion board: https://app.notion.com/p/39a1402af56080458673d2afa6c1cdc5 (data source `86f1402a-f560-826a-8ea0-07594e7d6759`)
4. Phase 0: analysis + **clarifying questions** before plan
5. Phase 1: master plan + **architectural questions** (physics, UI, scripts)
6. Phase 2: GATE → PLATFORM_SLICE | TARGET_BUILD per task

## Notion status (this cycle)

| Column | Who |
| ------ | --- |
| No Select (empty) | New/discovered tasks |
| To do | Orchestrator grooms next work |
| In progress → Review | Subagent (+ **commit before Review** for code) |
| Done / back to To do | **User** on board |

## Do not confuse with

- `@notion-create-task` — single ticket authoring, not full cycle
- `@notion-execute-task` — single Notion task, not orchestrator
- `@notion-ship-task` — commit ship when user says закоммить

## Orchestrator reply header

```markdown
**Cycle:** <phase> · **Active:** <task> · **Board:** [Iterative dev](https://app.notion.com/p/39a1402af56080458673d2afa6c1cdc5)
```
